Class RedFlag

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.timothy.bots.models.RedFlag

  • public class RedFlag
extends java.lang.Object
    A red flag that is on a red flag report. Very generic so it's easy to add new red flags later.

      • identifier

        public java.lang.String identifier
        The unique identifier is used to identify if we raised the same flag multiple times. It is unique to the report type. Ex: for use of /r/drugs it might be SUBREDDIT|drugs|Usage of /r/drugs

        Create a new red flag
        Parameters:
        id - the database id or -1 if not in the database yet
        reportId - the id of the RedFlagReport this is for
        type - the type of red flag this is
        identifier - an identifier for this flag for lookup
        description - the description markdown to be posted on reddit
        count - how many of this flag have been generated
        createdAt - when this red flag was created
